RD-OPS-001.title: Operational Modes & States Catalog

RD-OPS-002.title: Representative Operational Scenarios Set (Primary + Alternates)

PD-PRF-001.title: PD PRF 001: Top-Level Performance Parameter Budget (Sensitivity/Resolution Anchor)
PD-PRF-001.goal: Establish the phase-PD baseline set of top-level performance parameters (bands, WFE contributors, pointing/jitter contributors, throughput) and bind them to RD performance NFRs as the controlling budget anchors for downstream PD diagrams.

PD-OPT-001.title: PD OPT 001: Optical Wavefront Error (WFE) Allocation Budget (M1/M2/M3/APS/AO)
PD-OPT-001.goal: Allocate WFE contributors across optical train elements (M1 segments, M2, M3), alignment & phasing, and optional AO residuals, establishing explicit allocations and margins for PD baselining.

PD-OPT-002.title: PD OPT 002: End-to-End Throughput Budget (Optics + Instruments)
PD-OPT-002.goal: Define an end-to-end throughput budget across optical surfaces and instrument interfaces, including allocation per surface group and an overall minimum throughput target tied to sensitivity NFR.

PD-PT-001.title: PD PT 001: Pointing/Tracking Error Budget (Static + Dynamic)
PD-PT-001.goal: Allocate pointing and tracking error contributors (model error, encoder error, servo error, wind shake, structural flexure) and define roll-up to meet RD pointing/tracking functional and NFR constraints.

PD-PT-002.title: PD PT 002: Image Motion / Jitter Budget (Frequency-Banded)
PD-PT-002.goal: Budget jitter contributions by frequency band (e.g., low/mid/high) to match stability requirements and inform vibration control allocation.

PD-VIB-001.title: PD VIB 001: Structural Vibration & Windshake Allocation (Mount/Enclosure Coupling)
PD-VIB-001.goal: Quantify and allocate vibration/windshake contributions due to enclosure wind environment and mount/structure dynamics, providing parameters used by pointing/jitter budgets.

PD-TH-001.title: PD TH 001: Observatory Thermal Stability Budget (Optics + Enclosure + HVAC)
PD-TH-001.goal: Allocate thermal stability parameters (gradients, soak times, allowable deltas) that affect seeing/WFE and operational constraints, tied to environmental NFR.

PD-PWR-001.title: PD PWR 001: Electrical Power Budget (Steady-State + Peaks)
PD-PWR-001.goal: Create a power allocation across major subsystems with steady-state and peak/ transient loads, including safety-critical loads and backup behavior tie-ins.

PD-DATA-001.title: PD DATA 001: Data Rate & Volume Budget (Acquisition → Archive)
PD-DATA-001.goal: Budget raw data rates, metadata overhead, quick-look products, pipeline outputs, and archive ingest volumes to ensure feasibility against interface and data requirements.

PD-NET-001.title: PD NET 001: Network Bandwidth & Availability Budget (Onsite + External Links)
PD-NET-001.goal: Allocate network capacity and availability targets across onsite backbone, control/telemetry, and partner/external networks, tied to site interface requirements.

PD-TIM-001.title: PD TIM 001: Timing & Synchronization Budget (Time Source → Subsystems)
PD-TIM-001.goal: Parameterize time distribution accuracy, timestamping, and loop closure latencies across subsystems, ensuring consistency with timing NFR and interfaces.

PD-AVL-001.title: PD AVL 001: Availability Budget (Observing Time Loss Allocation)
PD-AVL-001.goal: Allocate observing time losses (weather, faults, maintenance, calibration overhead, startup/shutdown) to meet availability targets from ARM NFR and ops requirements.

PD-ARM-001.title: PD ARM 001: Reliability Allocation Budget (MTBF/Failure Rate by Subsystem)
PD-ARM-001.goal: Allocate reliability targets by subsystem (mount, optics control, enclosure, OCS, data, safety) to support overall availability modeling and verification planning.

PD-MNT-001.title: PD MNT 001: Maintainability & Service Time Budget (Segments/Instrument Swap)
PD-MNT-001.goal: Budget maintenance durations and frequencies for key maintainability drivers (segment handling, actuator calibration, instrument swaps) that impact availability and ops planning.

sample_names: "Planned maintenance time loss per observing period"
"Maintenance tasks only in allowed ops modes"
"Ensure the inclusion of instrument swap with correct subsystem references"

PD-IF-001.title: PD IF 001: Instrument Services Capacity Budget (Power/Data/Thermal/Control)
PD-IF-001.goal: Translate black-box instrument port requirements into allocated service capacities and margins per port/service category for PD baseline.

PD-SFTY-001.title: PD SFTY 001: Safety Integrity Budget (Interlock Coverage + Response Time)
PD-SFTY-001.goal: Quantify safety interlock response times, coverage allocations, and logging/audit retention parameters to support safety functional requirements and compliance NFRs.

PD-CAL-001.title: PD CAL 001: Calibration Overhead Budget (Time + Data + Cadence)
PD-CAL-001.goal: Budget calibration time overheads, cadences, and resulting data products/metadata impacts to ensure observing efficiency and data integrity targets.

PD-CFG-001.title: PD CFG 001: Configuration Variant Parameters (AO Optional + Instrument Modes)
PD-CFG-001.goal: Define a PD parameterization for key configuration variants (AO enabled/disabled, instrument class selection) to enable consistent budget switching without duplicating models.
